full_text: No matter how you slice it, tomorrow is my birthday. And I know what you’re thinking. Yes, even in Australia, tomorrow is my birthday (it is still today in Australia.)

what i loved about Everything, Everywhere, All At Once is that it fully took advantage of being a MOVIE. It reminded me of why I loved Sorry to Bother you. Fun, bold, wacky choices that were emboldened by editing, production design, costuming, all unique to the medium of film.

The Daniels’ “Interesting Ball” is a perfect short film also dabbling in multiverse theory and was (in my opinion) unfortunately released the same week as Too Many Cooks in 2014 and completely overshadowed.
